internalContents.title: * Define team members (101)
internalContents.description:
clmadmin created:
Summary Define team members
Description Define the team members for the project area as well as the team area

To define team members for a team area or project area:

1. Open the team area or project area editor by right-clicking on the project or team area in the Team Artifacts or Team Organization view and selecting Open.

2. On the Overview page of the editor, there is a Members section. To add a user to the team select the Add button. To create a new user and add them as a member of the team, select the Create button

3. If you clicked Add, in the Add Team Members dialog, select the user(s) you wish to add to your team or project area. If you clicked Create, define the new team member in the Create User wizard.

4. Consider what roles individuals working on your project will assume and what role-specific process should apply to each role. In addition, you will want to consider what permissions to grant to individuals in these roles. For additional details on using Jazz Team Process, consult the Getting Started with Projects, Teams, and Process help topic.

5. On Save of the editor you will be prompted to send invitations to the newly added team members. This allows you to configure an email invitation that is sent to the new team member. The new team member can accept the invitation with File->Accept Team Invitation.... The invitation will quickly setup their Eclipse workspace to work with the team. At any time you can invite team members to join the team by selecting the team member in the Members section, right click and select Invite to Join Team....

See any terms you don't recognize? You may also wish to consult the Glossary for the Rational solution for Collaborative Lifecycle Management.

internalContents.title: * Define permissions (102)
internalContents.description:
clmadmin created:
Summary Define permissions
Description Review and adjust the permissions to be used for the project

To review and adjust the permissions:

1. Open the project area editor by right-clicking on the project in the Team Artifacts or Team Organization view and selecting Open.

2. Go to the Process Configuration tab.

3. Select the Permissions node under Project Configuration, review and adjust the project level permissions.

4. Select the Permissions node under Team Configuration, review and adjust the team level permissions.

For additional details on defining permissions, consult the Permissions help topic.

internalContents.title: * Define categories and releases for work items (100)
internalContents.description:
clmadmin created:
Summary Define categories and releases for work items
Description Define categories and releases for work items. These values will then be available in the work item Filed Against and Found In fields.

To define the work item categories for the project area:

1. Open the Project Area Editor by right-clicking on the project area in the Team Artifacts or Team Organization view and selecting Open.

2. Go to the Work Item Categories tab.

3. Define categories for work items as well as associate categories with the team areas responsible for the category.

To define the releases to file work items against:

1. Go to the Releases tab of the Project Area Editor.

2. Add some releases to file work items against.

For additional details on using Jazz Work Items, consult the Getting Started with Work Items help topic.

See any terms you don't recognize? You may also wish to consult the Glossary for the Rational solution for Collaborative Lifecycle Management.

internalContents.title: * Define sprints/iterations (99)
internalContents.description:
clmadmin created:
Summary Define sprints/iterations
Description Define sprints/iterations

When the project area was initialized, an initial timeline "Main Development" was created. Within the timeline a hierarchy of iterations has been created for you.

To edit, delete, duplicate or add additional timelines and iterations:

1. Open the Project Area Editor by right-clicking on the project area in the Team Artifacts or Team Organization view and selecting Open.

2. Go to the Timelines section in the editor. To create a new iteration, use either the Create Iteration... action or the Duplicate... action on an existing iteration.

3. To define the start and end dates for an existing iteration, use the Edit Properties... action on an existing iteration.

For additional details on using Jazz Team Process, consult the Getting Started with Projects, Teams, and Process help topic.

internalContents.title: * Share code with Jazz Source Control (98)
internalContents.description:
clmadmin created:
Summary Share code with Jazz Source Control
Description Share code with Jazz Source Control

To share code in your Eclipse workspace with the Jazz stream created during process initialization:

1. Select a project you wish to share, right-click and select Team->Share Project...

2. In the Share Project Wizard, select Jazz Source Control and select Next.

3. If you have more than one repository connection, you will be prompted to choose one. On the Jazz Repository page, select the repository in which you created your project area and select Next.

4. On the Select Component page, you should see a repository workspace prefixed with the name of the project area you created.

Expand this repository workspace and you will see a component. Select this component and select Next. Review the ignored resources on the next page and then select Finish to share your code with the specified component and repository workspace.

5. Now that the code has been shared to your repository workspace, you need to deliver it from your workspace to the stream created during initialization of the process. To do this, open the Pending Changes view.

6. In the Pending Changes view, you should see one outgoing change from your repository workspace. Right-click on the repository workspace and select Deliver to deliver your code to the stream associated with your team.

For additional details on using Jazz Source Control, consult the Getting Started with Jazz Source Control help topic.

See any terms you don't recognize? You may also wish to consult the Glossary for the Rational solution for Collaborative Lifecycle Management.

internalContents.description:

Summary Define a new build
Description Define a new build

To define a new build for your team:

1. Open the Team Artifacts view and expand the node corresponding to your connected project area.

2. Right-click the Builds node and select New Build Definition and follow the prompts in the wizard.

For additional details on defining build definitions using the Build Definition wizard, consult the Getting Started with setting up Jazz Builds help topic.
